Prioritization logic:
1. Primary sort: (estimated_monthly_savings × confidence) — highest first
2. Secondary: tracking issues rank higher than their savings suggest (broken tracking corrupts all decisions)
3. Tertiary: lower effort_hours breaks ties (quick wins surface higher)

For each of the top 10, add these two fields to the existing finding object:
- "priority_rank": number 1-10 (1 = most important)
- "priority_rationale": one sentence explaining why this rank

